==English==

=== Noun ===
'''depression''' (countable and uncountable; plural: [[depressions]])

#Generally, an area that is lower, either in topography or pressure, than the surrounding area.
#In [[:w:Psychology|Psychology]] and [[:w:Psychotherapy|Psychotherapy]] 
#*a state of mind which results in a serious, long-term lowering of enjoyment of life or inablility to visualize a happy future
#*a period of feeling "the blues" which lasts longer than several weeks and may include ideation of self-inflicted injury or [[suicide]].
#In [[Meteorology]] an area of lowered air pressure that generally brings moist weather 
#*([[Hurricane|Hurricanes]] and [[tornado|tornadoes]] occur in areas of very low air pressure)
#a period of time where an economy suffers E.G the great depression (US history)

